Add descriptor attributes so metadata about file identity (or other uses) can be plumbed through

In order to support mmap of nexe, irt, and/or shared libraries, we
must know that the underlying file is effectively immutable -- a
promise made by the embedding environment -- so that we will be free
from modify-after-validation security bugs.  This is the first step
towards that -- we add attributes to NaclDesc objects, so that the
embedding environment (NaCl plugin in Chrome) can bless the
appropriate descriptors.

BUG= https://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3355

